Dear Sir or Madam, 

                  After-sales service is regrettably rare in the 
computer games business. After all, to take a cynical view, why 
spend money to help people who have already bought the game?.. 
They are not going to buy second copies. 

So perhaps it is not too surprising that Level 9 are still the only 
publishers that I know of giving away comprehensive free cluesheets 
for our adventure games; six years after we pioneered the idea. 

I've got quicker with practice, but it still costs about #2,000 
in time and printing to produce a new cluesheet. This may be money 
wasted, but I prefer to think that extras such as free cluesheets 
are one reason why Level 9 are still around after all these years. 


                  Cluesheets for Level 9's most recent games, 
"Lancelot" and "Ingrid's Back!" are both now available, and I 
enclose a copy of each. 


                       Best wishes, 


                                   Pete Austin 